;; ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
;; COMPLIANCE DIRECTIVE — 2026-07-14
;;
;; Alfred, mid-dispatch: "Add all of R7RS-small's features. No
;; diverging. Fix in book."
;;
;; This directive applies to every in-flight lane and every future
;; lane. Do not close a lane while your namespace has an R7RS-small
;; deviation that could be normalized instead.
;; ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

(directive
  :id "compliance-r7rs-small-first"
  :date "2026-07-14"
  :active #t
  :body
    "1. Sakura Scheme aims for R7RS-small compliance. If a feature exists
     in R7RS-small and we don't have it, add it — implement in JS
     alongside the existing base.js primitives.

     2. Where the reference manual (the book, docs/SAKURA-SCHEME-REFERENCE.slat)
     diverges from R7RS-small, FIX THE BOOK, not R7RS. If our reference
     uses a non-Scheme idiom, rewrite the reference. Do not add a
     non-Scheme feature to the interp.

     3. All previously-agreed decisions stand: positional args (no kw
     syntax in interp), no polymorphic `get`, shape-specific accessors
     (hash-ref/assoc/vector-ref/car-cdr).

     4. Any deliberate deviation from R7RS-small must be logged in
     docs/ENGINEERING-DECISIONS.slat with a decision-entry including
     what, why, and alternatives-rejected. No silent breaks.

     5. Every verb's :examples must use only R7RS-small forms (or forms
     documented in a decision-entry). If your examples use e.g. `get`
     or `:kw value` today, rewrite them.

     6. The R7RS-Compliance-Sweep lane (dispatched 2026-07-14) is doing
     the full audit + implementation of missing R7RS-small features.
     Its output lands in src/base.js and companion files. On git pull
     you may see new primitives arrive — use them.

     7. Trust Scheme. Alfred: 'They've tried things and talked about
     it longer than I have.'"
  :author "Alfred (via Claude, dispatch coordinator)"
  :supersedes ())
